  "stage": {
    "id": "course_advanced",
    "stageNumber": 3,
    "title": "Advanced: Training & Results",
    "roomWidth": 20,
    "roomHeight": 15,
    "concepts": [
      {
        "id": "causal_masking",
        "title": "Causal Masking: Preventing Future Cheating",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Mask future tokens\n- Prevents decoder from seeing output\n- Enables autoregressive generation\n\nDuring training, the decoder must not see future ground truth tokens. Causal masking sets future attention weights to -∞ before softmax, forcing attention to zero. This enables autoregressive generation at test time.",
        "position": {
          "x": 5,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "training_optimization",
        "title": "Training the Transformer",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- Warmup schedule\n- Adam optimizer\n- Dropout and label smoothing\n\nVaswani et al. use Adam optimizer with a custom schedule: linearly increase learning rate for 4000 warmup steps, then decay by steps^-0.5. Dropout (0.1) and label smoothing (ε=0.1) prevent overfitting. 12 hours on 8 P100 GPUs trains the base model.",
        "position": {
          "x": 9,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      },
      {
        "id": "machine_translation",
        "title": "Results: Machine Translation Excellence",
        "content": "Key ideas:\n- 28.4 BLEU on EN-DE\n- 41.8 BLEU on EN-FR\n- 3.5x faster training\n\nThe Transformer achieves state-of-the-art 28.4 BLEU (English-German) and 41.8 BLEU (English-French) on WMT 2014, training in just 3.5 days on 8 GPUs — much faster than previous RNN-based approaches.",
        "position": {
          "x": 13,
          "y": 6
        },
        "type": "text"
      }
    ],
